FilterParameters.description:
Specify the filter parameter values to be applied in reports. The JSON for the different types of parameters includes, 

 1. For String parameter - {"FilterParameters":"{\'SalesOrderNumber':['SO50750']}"} 

  2. For Integer parameter - {"FilterParameters":"{\'InvoiceID':['10252']}"} 

 3. For Date parameter - {"FilterParameters":"{\'StartDate':['1/1/2003'],\'EndDate':['1/31/2003']}"} 

 4. For Boolean parameter - {"FilterParameters":"{\'ReportParameter1':['true']}"} 

 The Date parameters input values are validated based on the server culture. Valid formats for en-us culture as following: `mm/dd/yyyy` `yyyy/mm/dd` `dd/mmm/yyyy` `mmm/dd/yyyy` `yyyy/dd/mmm` `yyyy/mmm/dd`.
